content.description: Pretty similar to "Awesome," but a little bit taller. Slabby topout with good holds and some fun moves. 2 variations on this one; you can go left or right.
content.location: 2nd from the right on the Upper Wall, to the left of "Awesome."

content.description: The further one gets towards the lower wall, the higher the band gets, the more climbing is available. Hence the bump in quality for this one. Fun slabby moves pretty much the whole way.
content.location: Third from the right, to the left of the "Slab Happy" variations, to the right of "Lonely Lover's Chimney."

content.description: This is the obvious chimney that is on the upper wall to the left of the first four problems. Home Water Birth is the the left of this. Squeeze up it if you're bored, or use it for the downclimb.

I was tempted to give this four stars since there are very cool holds on this at just the right spot, but it just doesn't flow as well as a four star should imo. Get on it and tell me what you think. Climb the arete and hold it together at the top. Exit rightish. A cool looking variation has yet to be done (that I know of) using both aretes.
content.location: The first route around the corner to the right from the lower wall.

content.description: Good holds lead shortly to a slabby topout.
content.location: Furthest problem on the right of the Upper Wall.

content.description: The Upper Wall is to the right and around the disappointingly chossy corner of the Postpartum Wall, and slightly uphill. This wall isn't quite as good as the lower, but still merits a looksie.
